						               													<description>King David: Miniature Battles in the Old Testament Period is a set of simple rules for wargaming the Battles of the Bible and other wars of the Ancient Near East up through the era of Troy.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game is scaled for 15mm miniatures but is easily adapted to 25/28mm figures by converting centimeters to inches.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game features include random terrain generation, pre-plotted hidden deployment, propitiatory acts, ambushes, variable initiative and movement determination, missile and melee combat, Heroes and Generals.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Army Lists are included for nineteen armies including multiple periods for peoples such as Israelites and Egyptians.  Unit types include Heavy and Light chariots, Heavy and Light infantry, a variety of missile troops, Cavalry, Camelry and a number of culture-specific troop types.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Individual unit initiative rolls make for a freewheeling and unpredictable game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
